This paper is about vehicle re-identification using computer vision techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses various design choices and optimization techniques used to achieve small and fast models, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of attention mechanisms and feature extraction techniques also relates to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the trade-offs between accuracy, model size, and speed, which is related to the security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
